summary: An email chain between FBI agents discussing a priority lead related to Jeffrey Epstein in California, specifically regarding the service of a grand jury subpoena to an individual. The communication highlights coordination between the San Francisco/Monterey Bay and New York FBI offices.

connections.description: FBI agents/officials coordinating on a priority Epstein investigation lead and subpoena service between California and New York offices.

events.title: Coordination for Epstein Subpoena Service
events.description: FBI Special Agent U contacts M in New York to discuss a priority Epstein lead in California, specifically regarding serving a grand jury subpoena to an individual.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively pursuing a priority lead related to Jeffrey Epstein in California as of July 2020.
A grand jury subpoena was being prepared for service to an individual in California in connection with the Epstein investigation.
There was coordination between the FBI's San Francisco/Monterey Bay and New York offices regarding this lead.
The communication indicates ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case nearly a year after Epstein's death.
